Subject: desktop bootstrap: install from release branch

The desktop first-launch bootstrap runner was written for upstream's source
layout, where `scripts/install.sh` and `scripts/install.ps1` exist at the same
Git commit that stamps the app bundle. In this fork, the stamped commit is the
workshop commit (`upstream/`, patches, overlay), while the runnable customer
tree and installer scripts live on the generated `release` branch.

Fetching `scripts/install.sh` from the source commit therefore 404s in a fresh
Nadia Agent.app launch. Even if that fetch used the release branch, passing the
source commit through as `--commit` would make the installer detach to the
workshop commit and install the wrong layout.

For desktop first-launch bootstrap, fetch the installer from the release branch
and run installer stages against the release branch. Keep the source commit only
as the build stamp/cache key and marker metadata.

